race.comment: This race is all about FAST HARRY (2) who looks a talented gelding in the making. He resumed with a dominant win here 18 days ago and he's expected to be better again now. He's probably a Saturday class horse in a CL3, and it's a scary prospect for his rivals that he could be better again now. HOBA METEOR (7) ran face first into Harry last start when only fairly away and ending up 3.8L off him at the finish. She is better than what she showed there however. With a better jump today, she can sit closer in the run and put herself into the finish. WHO SAZ YES (6) got the job done off a freshen last start when storming home from the back. She put up good figures in doing so there and while this is tougher, she should be better for that fresh effort. Watch for her late in the race again. MOLLY'S MY PAL (10) is racing well and is worth including while KING CARTEL (1) can turn in a bold effort from the front.
